      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "rationale": "Systematic grid convergence study on three mesh levels (3.2M, 12.8M, 51.2M cells) following ASME V&V 20 GCI methodology. GCI on NIH = 1.3% (fine-to-medium) and 5.1% (medium-to-coarse), confirming asymptotic convergence. Apparent order of convergence p = 1.91. All production simulations use the 12.8M cell mesh with GCI < 2% on NIH.",
