        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "GCI on primary QoI must be less than 5% on the production mesh. Three-level Richardson extrapolation must demonstrate asymptotic convergence (GCI ratio within 5% of unity)."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions documented in FDA benchmark protocol: fluid temperature 37 ± 0.5 °C, viscosity 3.5 ± 0.1 mPa·s, hematocrit 40 ± 1%. Flow rates measured with calibrated Coriolis meter (±0.5% FS). Rotational speed controlled to ±2 RPM. Inlet turbulence intensity measured via LDV. All conditions traceable to NIST-calibrated instruments.",
