      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is NIH (normalized index of hemolysis), which is the direct regulatory metric for hemolysis acceptance per ASTM F1841. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) are physically linked to NIH through the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. All QoIs are directly relevant to the clinical decision (chronic hemolysis risk).",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
