      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Turbulence modelled with SST k-ω; model selection justified by published benchmark comparisons for rotating machinery flows (Baldwin et al. 2021). Hemolysis sub-model uses Giersiepen-Wurzinger power law with coefficients calibrated to RBC lysis data. Model form uncertainty estimated via comparison of three turbulence models (k-ε, SST k-ω, RSM); NIH variation < 8% across models, bounded within UQ intervals.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
